{"meta":{"updateDate":1755117017724,"pPcc":"SAT#H","questionId":"9d9fe1e6","skill_cd":"H.B.","score_band_range_cd":2,"skill_desc":"Linear functions","createDate":1755117017724,"program":"SAT","primary_class_cd_desc":"Algebra","ibn":"","external_id":"d06b80b0-bba8-4218-bf79-f285777b8fbc","primary_class_cd":"H","uId":"97539577-d512-471e-9633-4f4426dc5c5a","difficulty":"E"},"source":"modern","detail":{"type":"mcq","stem":"<p style=\"text-align: left;\">In science class, Diego conducted an experiment to learn about evaporation. Diego measured the height of fluid in a beaker over a period of time. The function <math alttext=\"f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals 39 minus 0.18 x\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>39</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0.18</mn><mi>x</mi></math> gives the estimated height, <math alttext=\"in centimeters left parenthesis cm right parenthesis\"><mtext>in</mtext><mo>&#160;</mo><mtext>centimeters</mtext><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced><mtext>cm</mtext></mfenced></math>, of the fluid in the beaker <math alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi>\n</math> days after the start of the experiment. Which of the following is the best interpretation of <math alttext=\"39\"><mn>39</mn>\n</math> in this context?</p>","keys":["04be94f2-099d-490b-87bc-dfbd726734ab"],"answerOptions":[{"id":"04be94f2-099d-490b-87bc-dfbd726734ab","content":"<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The estimated height, <math alttext=\"in cm\"><mtext>in</mtext><mo>&#160;</mo><mtext>cm</mtext></math>, of the fluid at the start of the experiment</p>"},{"id":"1b70658a-b58b-429d-b383-b77c19d252de","content":"<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The estimated height, <math alttext=\"in cm\"><mtext>in</mtext><mo>&#160;</mo><mtext>cm</mtext></math>, of the fluid at the end of the experiment</p>"},{"id":"11299118-dec0-476a-bf81-78e07f89f037","content":"<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The estimated change in the height, <math alttext=\"in cm\"><mtext>in</mtext><mo>&#160;</mo><mtext>cm</mtext></math>, of the fluid each day</p>"},{"id":"ec6a11ba-8381-4748-b7ef-be310378f798","content":"<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The estimated number of days for all the fluid to evaporate</p>"}],"rationale":"<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice A is correct. It’s given that the function&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals 39 minus 0.18 x\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>39</mn><mo>−</mo><mn>0.18</mn><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;gives the estimated height, in centimeters (cm), of the fluid in the beaker&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi></math> days after the start of the experiment. For a function defined by an equation of the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals b plus m x\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>x</mi></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"m\"><mi>m</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\"><mi>b</mi></math> are constants,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\"><mi>b</mi></math> represents the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f left parenthesis x right parenthesis\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x equals 0\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>. It follows that in the given function, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"39\"><mn>39</mn></math> represents the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f left parenthesis x right parenthesis\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x equals 0\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>. Since <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x equals 0\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> represents the start of the experiment, then the best interpretation of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"39\"><mn>39</mn></math> in this context is that the estimated height, in cm, of the fluid was <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"39\"><mn>39</mn></math> at the start of the experiment.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice B is incorrect and may result from conceptual errors.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice C is incorrect. The estimated change in the height, in cm, of the fluid each day is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"0.18\"><mn>0.18</mn></math>, not <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"39\"><mn>39</mn></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual errors.</p>","externalid":"d06b80b0-bba8-4218-bf79-f285777b8fbc","correct_answer":["A"]}}